                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/cre">Creator</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>A petition to the International Fraternity of Delta Sigma Pi by Alpha Beta Mu, the University of Tulsa, Tulsa, Oklahoma 1948.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>Bound petition from the Alpha Beta Mu business fraternity at the Univerity of Tulsa requesting a chapter of Delta Sigma Pi be established at the University. The item is divided into chapters which include the petition to Delta Sigma Pi, signed by all the members of Alpha Beta Mu, history of Tulsa, the University of Tulsa, the College of Business Administration, Alpha Beta Mu, with brief biographies of each member, including portrait. The final chapter is letters of recommendation from various University and business officials. Each chapter heading is hand-lettered in gold on heavy patterned card stock. The text is typed and profusely illustrated iwth photograph and other illustrations tipped in. Included with the volume is a copy of the invitation sent to Alpha Beta Mu members requesting their presence at the installation of the Beta chi chapter of Delta Sigma Pi, Sunday, May 9th, 1948. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Tulsa City-County Library</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>

                  </name>
                  <titleInfo>
                     <title>Lambda Tau, Beta Chapter archive, 1939-1986.</title>
                  </titleInfo>
                  <abstract>The archive contains material such as drafts of the constitution and by-laws for both national and local groups, a brief history of the Oklahoma chapters, Beta Chapter's application for recognition by the national society, installation ceremonies, meeting minutes, correspondence, membership records, The Lambda Tau Newsletter (1965-1986) and a scrapbook containing photos and press cuttings. Also included is material relating to Mu Tau Phi, the local society which preceeded Lambda Tau at the University of Tulsa. </abstract>
                  <name>
                     <namePart>Tulsa City-County Library</namePart>
                     <role>
                        <roleTerm valueURI="http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/rps">Repository</roleTerm>
                     </role>
                  </name>
               </mods>
            </objectXMLWrap>

Also included is material relating to Mu Tau Phi, the local society which preceeded Lambda Tau at the University of Tulsa.
